 Confucianism can address the individual as well as the communal and serve as a philosophy for contemporary times.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aConfucian ethics. 0aPhilosophy, ChinesexTo 221 B.C. 0aPhilosophy, ChineseyTo 221 B.C. 0aPhilosophy, ConfucianxChinaxChina. 0aPhilosophy, ConfucianzChina. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Confucianism. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Eastern / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2016z978311149098440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846150240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438461502423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438461502/original  a978-3-11-149098-4  SUNY Press eBook Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles